		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 12/14/2002 12:52:39 AM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=56896">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for TooCrooked" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="mailto:toocrooked@mail.com" target="_new">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/email.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Email TooCrooked" width="24" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=TooCrooked">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message TooCrooked" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=99&FN=Rallos+Zek&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1804278&TN=why+does+PvP+fail+on+EQ%3F&CAT=Servers&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1804278&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">people seem to have many conceptions on why PvP is so flawed in EQ. out of the many i have read, the one that seems to stand out the most is the reliance of a person on their gear.</P><P>i have never played AC or UO, but i hear that the PvP system here is well implemented. is it because a person's stats are based on their character, and much less on their gear?</P><P>the way i see it, there is too much to gain (and lose) from an encounter on rallos. i dont find it fair that someone can zone camp you and take your shoulder item when all they did was hit you a few times.. its not even totally HOW they killed you, but rather how much they gained from such a trivial encounter.</P><P>from the stance SOE takes on EQ, the whole "risk VS reward thing", it would seem that PvP is the absolute opposite of this. it seems like its a server made that both skill and totally explotation are rewarded the same. and at some point, the line gets skewed, because as we all know, most choose the path of least resistance.</P><P>all this to say that since skill and explotation are both rewarded fairly equally (you get to gank an item in either case), its obvious that more people will choose the easier way (in this case, what i like to call exploiting, since thats most time what it comes down to), and not be skillful.</P><P>thus, the downfall of eq pvp. a flawed "risk vs reward" system due to an over-reliance on gear in the game. its not that PvP isnt FUN, its that its absolutely incompatible with EQ.</P><P>am i wrong?<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
