		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1"><BR> No, you're not wrong at all. The truth is, there is no "risk vs. reward" balance whatsoever on Rallos. It all comes down to four basic things - your class, your gear, your enemy's hp/mana level, and in a very distant fourth, your skill. Simply put, all of Verant's biggest mistakes come crashing down on you twicefold if you play EQ pvp. For one thing, the large imbalance between casters/melees causes a HUGE disparity in pvp "skill". And 99% of the pvp encounters on Rallos involve no skill on the part of the attacker at all. A naked caster (bound himself right near pk encounter, full mana, no gear to lose in the possibility of death) can EASILY decimate a low-hp melee (bound far, far away in some distant city, full complement of armor to be looted) by simply exploiting (i.e. levitating to the top of a cliff where melee can't attack caster). At least, Verant calls that exploiting if it's done against a mob. /shrug.</P><P>    -Zan</P><P> I support the removal of all anonymous posting restrictions on everlore. If you feel as I do, please include this in your signature.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
