		<hr size="1">Well, Crooked...not REALLY so much on your topic here, but I really liked how the pvp was implmented on Meridian 59, if you remember that one...</P><P>....you strike someone out of a duel, and they DONT die, your name goes orange. if you die with an orange name you go back to white....or you can quest it away. The quests were odd, and NOT easy to do...you became an outlaw</P><P>....a white name or an orange name could kill you and they would not go on to the next category...below...</P><P>If you kill someone, pk or otherwise, your name goes red...at that point you're free game for everyone, and the only way to get rid of your red name was to "petition" a GM, AND have backup from a number of players...and even then the petition times were spread far apart...I think it was once a month. Players heard the explanation, and acted as "judges" , and if they bought it you had your name changed back to white. Red a second time meant you were red forever...a murderer...</P><P>...re-roll...or be a PK and be hunted....</P><P>Thats a watered down explanation, but you get the idea, if you didnt already know...</P><P>I always thought it was a neat system, and one which could have been implemented on all the servers in EQ. Or some of em'....whatever..but its something that should have been tried at least...</P><P>....comments?</P><P>Val's wife...</P><P>Aka Vicky on 105<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
