		<hr size="1">I think it’s only a failure from the aspect that there is no real team concept. Banding together in a common purpose could lead to one helluva a time in PvP under the right circumstances. This is odd to me because the idea behind EQ – which I always hated – has been to “promote grouping.” But Tallon and vallon fall short and are not completely thought out, in my opinion.</P><P>I think there should always be servers like Rallos and Sullon though. That way you can have those that are anti by day/ganker by night on Rallos, and bored higher levels on Sullon that can run around and kill just to be a pain in the ass. There are always going to be unskilled cowards in the game just like in real life. There should be a collection point for them so they can feed on each other.</P><P>However, for the rest of us who want a game including PvP that is about cunning, daring, guts, and brains, and not just how much gear I can throw on a guy, there ought to be a place for us as well.</P><P>Mr. Anon, it’s not whining to want a game designed to maximize a player’s skill, and not his ability to own gear far beyond their level. I believe there’s a way to do this, but I’m not exactly sure how. Ergo... THE FREAKIN' DISCUSSION, ya moe-ron.</P><P>Also, Mr. Anon, if you don’t have the courage to register, I can only assume you’re part of the problem. Take the fungi off, and register. If you want to join the debate, join it like a man. Otherwise, butt the hell out.</P><P>PS</P><P>Whatever happened to that sub-human douche bag, Malakan? He still play? <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/happy.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
