		<hr size="1">Well, TooCrooked its like this, pvp in EQ works great - on paper.  In game its another thing entirely because of the way players use it.  In an average pvp encounter you would probably be resting after killing an npc when you are suddenly mezzed, tashed and blinded by a chanter then and nuked by his wiz buddy.  PKs always have the advantage when then are hunting because they get themselves well prepared and wait until their target is at his weakest.  They also have the advantage of getting the first spell cast off on an opponent that is low hp / mana and probably has an npc targeted at the time they are attacked. 90% of darkenbane were d***heads, only about 10% would actually pvp fairly i.e. one on one against an opponent with full hp.  The curse are the lowest of the low, they spend their entire time doing newbie quests to build up faction and then exploit that faction against anyone who happens to come along.  They try to get the kill in before their victim takes an exp death from an agroed guard but their pvp skills are so lame they end up getting the player exp killed 80% of the time.  RoP are like the lame 90% of darkenbane, great in numbers against a single opponent but owned in any other situation.</P><P>In short, if you want player vs player then play halflife, quake, unreal or any of those online FPS because they require more skill than pvp on EQ.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
